<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,1996,2059]" lastBlockId="3.[136,1452,158,256]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="168" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">
The type is characterized by whitish thallus with semiglobose, in part sorediate, scattered or crowded warts. The thallus is zoned at the margin. Soralia with granular soredia are very frequent, whitish to greenish grey (
<figureCitation box="[1196,1293,2032,2059]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[136,234,1136,1158]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,190,1112]" captionTargetId="figure-24@2.[151,1436,190,1112]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lectotype of Pertusaria jurana in HBG." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5423925" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5423925/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="167">Figure 2</figureCitation>
). The analysis of secondary metabolites (
<collectionCode box="[427,483,158,184]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">TLC</collectionCode>
) showed the presence of fatty acids. 
<taxonomicName box="[889,1089,159,184]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Pertusariaceae" genus="Pertusaria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pertusariales" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="jurana">
<emphasis box="[889,1089,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">Pertusaria jurana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[1318,1452,158,184]" name="Switzerland" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
and the name has later been reported from Europe only (
<bibRefCitation author="Erichsen, C. F. E." box="[756,918,194,221]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" pagination="321 - 701" refId="ref2932" refString="Erichsen, C. F. E. (1935 [1936]) Pertusariacae. In: Zahlbruckner, A. (ed.) Dr. L. Rabenhorsts Kryptogamenflora von Deutchland, Osterreich und der Schweiz. Leipzig, Akademische Verlagsgesellschaft. 9 (5) [1]: 321 - 701." type="journal article" year="1935">Erichsen 1935</bibRefCitation>
[
<bibRefCitation author="Erichsen, C. F. E." box="[931,994,194,221]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" pagination="77 - 101" refId="ref2989" refString="Erichsen, C. F. E. (1936) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Flechtengattung Pertusaria. Feddes Repertorium 41: 77 - 101. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / fedr. 19360410105" type="journal article" year="1936">1936</bibRefCitation>
]; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hocevar, S. &amp; Batic, F. &amp; Piskernik, M. &amp; Martincic, A." box="[1012,1233,194,221]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" pagination="319" refId="ref3194" refString="Hocevar, S., Batic, F., Piskernik, M. &amp; Martincic, A. (1995) Glive v pragozdovih Slovenije. Strokovna in znanstvena dela 117. Gozdarski Institut Slovenije, Ljubljana, p. 319." type="book chapter" year="1995">
Hocevar 
<emphasis box="[1113,1168,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="168">et al.</emphasis>
1995
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Faltynowicz, W." box="[1243,1447,194,220]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" pagination="1 - 435" refId="ref3027" refString="Faltynowicz, W. (2003) The lichens, lichenicolous and allied fungi of Poland. An annotated checklist. In: Mirek, Z. (Ed.) Biodiversity of Poland 6. W. Szafer Institute of Botany of Polish Academy of Sciences, Krakow, pp. 1 - 435." type="book chapter" year="2003">Fałtynowicz 2003</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Clerc, P." box="[136,264,230,256]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" pagination="1 - 320" refId="ref2720" refString="Clerc, P. (2004) Les champignons lichenises de Suisse, catalogue bibliographique complete par des donnees sur la distribution et l'ecologie des especes. Cryptogamica Helvetica 19: 1 - 320." type="journal article" year="2004">Clerc 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Knezevic, B. &amp; Mayrhofer, H." box="[274,604,230,256]" pageId="3" pageNumber="168" pagination="283 - 328" refId="ref3293" refString="Knezevic, B. &amp; Mayrhofer, H. (2009) Catalogue of the lichenized and lichenicolous fungi of Montenegro. Phyton 48: 283 - 328." type="journal article" year="2009">Knežević &amp; Mayrhofer 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
